        "Pediatric_GCS[1]": {
          "text": "Note:\nFor Motor score 4, pain is defined flat, fingernail pressure (often performed with the barrel of a pencil).\nFor Motor scores 2 and 3, pain is defined by pressing hard on the supraorbital notch. If this unsuccessful, sternal pressure may also be attempted.",
